                            <comment id="13596872" author="abozanich" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2013 06:22:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;use iterateNonZero() when vector is not dense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13598630" author="ssc" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 08:17:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing us, there are much more problems in that code...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; nzero = 0;
    Iterator&amp;lt;Vector.Element&amp;gt; iterateNonZero = v.iterateNonZero();
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (iterateNonZero.hasNext()) {
      iterateNonZero.next();
      nzero++;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;can be replaced by v.getNumNonDefaultElements() for example...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
